rComments: Perhaps one of the best classes I have taken. Also, one of the best professors ever. TAKE HIS CLASS IF YOU HAVEN'T!
Great professor.He explains everything clearly in the lecture. Also, he is friendly and helpful. However, the test is a little bit hard. Well, don't worry, there is a curve.
Good teacher. He cares about his students and he tries to connect with them.

My favorite professor at U of I. He teaches clearly, he cares about students, and he is so willing to help. Office hours are great. MATH 453 had weekly homework assignments that were moderately hard, but with office hours I almost always knew the answers and they went much more quickly. Fair grading, very clear about what's on the tests.
